==List vTerminal ==
This operation is used to list vTerminal information based on specified conditions.


===Request===

{| class="wikitable"
|-
| Method || GET
|-
| Request URI   || 
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vterminals
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vterminals/detail
/vtns/{vtn_name}/vterminals/count
|- 
| Query string ||
 ?index={vterminal_name}
 &max_repetition={max_repetition}
|}

;Description of request URI elements

{|class="wikitable"
|-
| Element || Description || Required
|-
|vtn_name || VTN name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including
alphanumeric characters and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||Yes
|}
;Description of query string elements

{| class="wikitable"
|-
| Element || Description || Required
|-
|vterminal_name || vTerminal name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including
alphanumeric characters and underscore (except at the
beginning).
||No
|-
|max_repetetion || Number of the resources that are returned.Valid value: A positive integer Valid range: 1 to MAX of UINT32. Default is 10000
||No
|}

=== Response ===

: The Response returned will be one of the values in the [[OpenDaylight Virtual Tenant Network (VTN):VTN Coordinator:RestApi|List of response Codes]].
 
;Response Body 
{| class="wikitable"
|-
| Response Body (XML)  ||
If count or detail is not specified in URI
  <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
  <vterminals>
    <vterminal vterminal_name="{vterminal_name}"/>
  </vterminals>
If detail is specified in URI
 <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
 <vterminals>
   <vterminal vterminal_name="{vterminal_name}" controller_id="{cont
 roller_id}" domain_id="{domain_id}" description="{description}" stat
 us="{status}"/>
 </vterminals>
If count is specified in URI
 <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
 <vterminals count="{count}"/>
|-
| Request Body (JSON) ||
If count or detail is not specified in URI
 {
  "vterminals": [
   {
        "vterminal_name": "{vterminal_name}"
    }
   ]
 }
If detail is specified in URI
 {
   "vterminals": [ 
    {
     "vterminal_name": "{vterminal_name}",
     "controller_id": "{controller_id}",
     "domain_id": "{domain_id}",
     "description": "{description}",
     "status": "{status}"
    }
   ]
 }
If count is specified in URI
 {
   "vterminals": {
       "count": "{count}"
   }
 }
|}

;Description of Response Elements

{| class="wikitable"
|-
| Element || Description 
|-
|vterminal_name || vTerminal name.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including alphanumeric
characters and underscore (except at the beginning).
|-
|controller_id || Controller ID.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including alphanumeric
characters and underscore (except at the beginning).
|-
|domain_id || Domain ID.
Valid value: Up to 31 characters including alphanumeric
characters and underscore (except at the beginning), and the
string "(DEFAULT)".
Note: "(DEFAULT)" indicates default domain.
|-
|description || Additional information.
Valid value: Up to 127 characters.
|-
|status || vTerminal status.
Valid value: up, down, unknown
|-
|count || Number of the vTerminals.
Valid value: Decimal number.
|}


